    <article>
        <h2>How it started</h2>
        Games are how I got started with computers. I programmed using a, then new, program called GameMaker. With that I came to understand
        the complex world of Game Design and Game Programming. This basic drag and drop game development helps usher me into scripting with
        its built in scripting language called GML. From that my curiosity came out to figure out how the program itself works. I went on to
        learn C++ my first program involved using OpenGl to render a sprite and then, using the skills I already obtained from GameMaker, I
        created a basic mario platformer. I soon learned CollisionDetection algorithms and how to manage memory. From that I went on to look into
        homebrew development on the WII. Creating a custom launcher for games as well as a animation class to help animate the menu. Soon I was
        looking into what it would take to develop games for a living, I learned how to use the XDA development kit for the Xbox360 learning C# along the way.
        After that I decided the future was going to be in mobile and web development. 2 years ago I started to learn HTML, Javascript, PHP, MYSQL, Node.js and
        various other languages/libraries which helped launch me onto creating this site. And I am STILL learning how to improve this site. Check
        out the history of this site by following the Code link at the bottom of the site.
    </article>
